## 5. Coding Standards and Formatting

### Language and Comments
- Write all comments in English
- Add comments for complex code blocks
- Use descriptive variable and function names

### Encoding and Formatting
- Use UTF-8 for all files
- Indentation: Use tabs for all file types
- Empty lines between code blocks
- Consistent formatting throughout

### Browser Compatibility
- Maintain compatibility with browsers from browserslist in package.json
- Use semantic versioning
- Document changes in README.md

## 6. Performance and Optimization

### Image Optimization
- Optimize images before adding to project
- Use WebP format where possible
- Add alt attributes for all images
- Use descriptive, kebab-case filenames

### Caching and HTTP Requests
- Minimize HTTP requests through concatenation
- Use gulp-rev for caching
- Optimize resource loading order

### Build Optimization
- Development: Source maps, unminified files
- Production: Minified, optimized, cached files
- Backend: Specific build for backend integration

## 7. Security and Validation

### Code Validation
- Validate HTML through node-w3c-validator
- Check code for standards compliance
- Use editorconfig for consistency

### External Resources
- Use HTTPS for CDN resources
- Add integrity attributes for external scripts
- Verify security of third-party libraries

